toLowerCase() method==>
                       This method is used to convert the string into lowercase letter. This method doesn't make any change in the original string.
syntax==>
          var str=str1.toLowerCase();
Example==>
<html>
<body>
<script type="text/javascript">
var  str="Archana";
document.write("Original string:"+str);
var str1=str.toLowerCase();
document.write("<br>New string:"+str1);
</script>
</body>
</html>

Example 2:-
<html>
<body>
<script type="text/javascript">
var  str="KhUsHi";
document.write("Original string:"+str);
var str1=str.toLowerCase();
document.write("<br>New string:"+str1);
</script>
</body>
</html>
